(Part of [[Open Source Transport Informatics tools]] listing, for the [[OSSTIP]] project, especially [[OSSTIP/WP2- Transit Informatics tools review]].)

The Open Source Accessibility Toolkit is a small package that helps calculate metrics of urban accessibility via different modes of transport, primarily developed by the not-for-profit organisation [http://noblis.org/ Noblis]. It uses [[OpenTripPlanner]] for the bulk of the transport routing work via public transport.

